            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Admin Time Corrections\n\nPast-dated or locked entries cannot be edited or deleted from the main grid — they are amended through admin corrections, which preserve an audit trail instead of mutating history silently.\n\n- **Endpoint:** `PATCH /api/v1/time-tracking/entries/{id}/correct`. Restricted to `Admin, Manager` roles (capability `CAP-HR-TIMETRACK`).\n- **Audit row:** every correction writes a `TimeCorrectionLog` row capturing the original values, the corrected values, the actor, and a **required** `Reason`. The source `TimeEntry` is updated in place; the log is the immutable record of what changed.\n- **Correctable fields:** `Date`, `DurationMinutes`, start/end times, `Category`, `Notes`, and `JobId` (job reassignment). Any subset may be supplied; omitted fields are left unchanged.\n- **History view:** `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/corrections` (also `Admin, Manager`) lists the correction log for review.\n- **Why not just delete + re-add:** deleting loses the original timestamp and breaks the audit chain. Corrections are the only sanctioned path for past entries so payroll and job-costing totals remain reconcilable.\n\n## Pay Periods, Locking & Overtime Config\n\nTime entries roll up into pay periods, and a closed period freezes its entries so downstream payroll math is stable.\n\n- **Current period:** `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/pay-period` returns the active `PayPeriod` (`type`, `periodStart`, `periodEnd`, `daysRemaining`). Period `type` is configurable — weekly, bi-weekly, semi-monthly, or monthly.\n- **Period settings:** `PUT /api/v1/time-tracking/pay-period/settings` (role `Admin` only) sets the period type and anchor.\n- **Locking:** `POST /api/v1/time-tracking/lock-period` (`Admin, Manager`) sets `IsLocked = true` on every entry in the range. Locked entries render a lock icon, refuse edits/deletes, and require an admin correction to change.\n- **Overtime rules:** `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/overtime-rules` (`Admin, Manager`) lists rules; `POST /api/v1/time-tracking/overtime-rules` (`Admin`) creates one. An `OvertimeRule` carries `dailyThresholdHours`, `weeklyThresholdHours`, `overtimeMultiplier` (e.g. 1.5x), optional `doubletimeThresholdDailyHours` / `doubletimeThresholdWeeklyHours` / `doubletimeMultiplier`, an `isDefault` flag, and `applyDailyBeforeWeekly` (ordering of daily-vs-weekly overtime accrual).\n- **Per-user breakdown:** `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/overtime/{userId}` (`Admin, Manager`) returns an `OvertimeBreakdown` — `regularHours` / `overtimeHours` / `doubletimeHours`, matching cost fields, and a `dailyBreakdown` array (`DailyOvertimeDetail` per day).\n\n## Shop-Floor & Mobile Clock-In\n\nClock events (presence) are captured outside the main Time Tracking page — on the shop-floor kiosk and the mobile clock — and are distinct from time entries (work performed).\n\n- **Kiosk:** the full-screen shop-floor clock lives at `/display/shop-floor/clock`. Identification is by **badge / RFID / barcode scan followed by PIN**; the kiosk also shows current worker clock status.\n- **Mobile:** the mobile clock page posts to `POST /api/v1/display/shop-floor/clock`.\n- **Event shape:** a `ClockEvent` records `eventTypeCode` (`clock-in`, `clock-out`, `break-start`, `break-end` — driven by the `clock_event_type` reference-data group), `timestamp`, `scanMethod` (RFID / barcode / manual / NFC), `source` (which device/kiosk), and an optional `reason`.\n- **Read/write:** `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/clock-events` and `POST /api/v1/time-tracking/clock-events`; `GET /api/v1/time-tracking/clock-status` returns the caller's current clocked state.\n- **Boundary:** clock events establish that an employee was on-site; time entries record what they worked on during that presence. They complement each other but are stored and edited separately.\n\n## Time → Job Costing & Payroll (Labor/Burden, QBO Sync)\n\nEach time entry feeds two downstream consumers: job cost rollups and payroll.\n\n- **Job costing:** when an entry has a `JobId` (set automatically when a timer starts from a job's kanban detail panel), its `LaborCost` (employee rate x duration) is applied to that job's cost rollup. `BurdenCost` tracks the overhead/burden allocation separately. `OperationId` enables operation-level costing within a job, and `EntryType` (`Setup`, `Run` default, `Teardown`, `Inspection`, `Rework`, `Wait`, `Other`) distinguishes the kind of operation time being tracked.\n- **Payroll:** entries within a pay period feed payroll totals, with overtime split per the active `OvertimeRule`. Payroll data is pushed via `POST /api/v1/payroll/sync` (capability `CAP-HR-PAYROLL`); pay stubs and tax documents are surfaced under the same controller.\n- **QuickBooks (QBO) sync:** when QBO is connected, a time entry can sync as a QuickBooks **Time Activity**; the external id is stored on `AccountingTimeActivityId` (null when unsynced). This is the accounting-boundary integration point — see `IAccountingService` / `AccountingTimeActivity`.\n- **Capability gating:** all Time Tracking endpoints require `CAP-HR-TIMETRACK`; payroll endpoints require `CAP-HR-PAYROLL`. Admin-only writes (pay-period settings, overtime-rule creation) are additionally role-gated.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Time Tracking training modules");
    }
